default2default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHow resilient are the UK’s transport networks (including road, rail and air) to adverse winter weather?default&#xa0;
default2.1
default&#xa0; 
defaultIt is vital that airport operators, airlines, surface transport providers, and government agencies co-ordinate more effectively to ensure that where transport is affected by adverse weather, the impact on passengers is minimised. For example, where airline
default operations are disrupted and airlines have the opportunity to recover by extending operations late into the night, it is vital that services such as surface transport provision and immigration facilities remain operational in order to minimise the risk of
default further disruption to customers. 
default&#xa0;default&#xa0;default3default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWhat lessons have been learned since the severe weather experienced in the winter of 2009-10?default&#xa0;default3.1
